Dia. 04 Opponent's Vital Point
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;\red255\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par From the beginning, how should White attack?
\par
\par White 1 is the \cf1\b 1-2 point \cf0\b0 and it follows the proverb which says: \cf2\b the opponent's vital point is my vital point\cf0\b0 .
\par
\par If Black plays at 2, blocking at 3 is good and Black is dead.
\par
\par
\par }
